DISTRIBUTION

How an auth-service version reaches its consumer — the dev/daemon
branch's services/auth-service/ directory.

auth-service is not published as a downloadable artifact. It is built
on its own branch (dev/auth-service) and the packager output is
committed back to dev/daemon by GitHub Actions. This keeps the
phantom-daemon source tree small per branch while preserving easy
traceability of where every change in services/auth-service/ came
from — only the github-actions[bot] account writes to that path.


Pipeline overview
-----------------

  1. Bump         Local script bumps __version__ on dev/auth-service
                  and creates a single commit.
  2. Verify       Push the bump commit. The test workflow runs the
                  full pytest suite on every push to dev/auth-service.
  3. Package      Operator runs package.sh, which dispatches the
                  package workflow with no arguments.
  4. Build        Workflow extracts version from auth_service/__init__.py,
                  then runs scripts/packager.py to produce a clean
                  dist/phantom-auth/ tree.
  5. Sync         Workflow checks out dev/daemon and replaces
                  services/auth-service/ with the packager output.
  6. Commit       Workflow commits "Build: Update auth-service to
                  v<VERSION>" as github-actions[bot] and pushes to
                  dev/daemon.
  7. Consumption  phantom-daemon's Docker build picks up the updated
                  services/auth-service/ on its next build.


Stage 1 — Bump
--------------

  .github/scripts/bump.sh [major|minor|patch]

  Defaults to patch. Reads __version__ from auth_service/__init__.py,
  bumps the chosen segment, writes back, verifies, and creates a
  single commit:

      Bump v<NEW_VERSION>

  Single source of truth — there is no Go/Rust counterpart to keep
  in sync.


Stage 2 — Verify
----------------

  git push origin dev/auth-service

  Triggers test-auth-service.yml automatically. The full pytest
  suite runs (auth, RBAC, audit, rate-limit, JWT, TOTP, …). Failure
  blocks nothing automatically — but operators do not dispatch
  package.sh on a red build.


Stage 3 — Package trigger
-------------------------

  .github/scripts/package.sh

  No arguments. Reads __version__ from auth_service/__init__.py for
  the operator-visible header, then dispatches
  package-auth-service.yml on the dev/auth-service ref via the
  GitHub CLI (gh workflow run).

  No version is passed — the workflow re-reads the same source file
  at runtime so there is exactly one truth.


Stage 4 — Package workflow
--------------------------

  package-auth-service.yml does the build + cross-branch sync in a
  single job. Steps in order:

      Checkout auth-service-src   The dev/auth-service branch as-is
                                  (read-only credentials).

      Checkout dev/daemon         The destination branch with write
                                  credentials (persist-credentials:
                                  true).

      Setup Python 3.12

      Extract version             Reads __version__ from
                                  auth-service-src/auth_service/__init__.py
                                  and validates X.Y.Z format. Aborts
                                  the run on mismatch.

      Build package               Runs python scripts/packager.py
                                  --clean inside auth-service-src.
                                  Produces dist/phantom-auth/ — a
                                  flat tree containing auth_service/,
                                  tools/setup.sh, tools/bootstrap.py,
                                  Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,
                                  requirements.in, requirements.txt.
                                  Tests, dev-only files, and caches
                                  are excluded.

      Sync to dev/daemon          rm -rf daemon/services/auth-service
                                  then cp -r
                                  auth-service-src/dist/phantom-auth
                                  daemon/services/auth-service. The
                                  destination directory is overwritten
                                  in full every run so removed files
                                  on the source side disappear from
                                  the target too.

      Commit and push             Configures git as github-actions[bot],
                                  stages services/auth-service,
                                  commits "Build: Update auth-service
                                  to v<VERSION>", pushes to dev/daemon.
                                  Gracefully no-op if the diff is
                                  empty (re-running the same version
                                  does not produce an empty commit).

      Summary                     Job summary reports file count and
                                  the target path.


Stage 5 — Consumption
---------------------

  phantom-daemon (dev/daemon branch) consumes auth-service via the
  services/auth-service/ directory, which is mounted into the
  daemon's compose stack at runtime.

  There is no fetch script, no R2 download, no artifact pull — the
  package is committed directly into the consumer branch. Updates
  surface on dev/daemon as "Build: Update auth-service to vX.Y.Z"
  commits authored by github-actions[bot].


End-to-end example
------------------

  # On dev/auth-service:
  $ .github/scripts/bump.sh patch
  1.1.1 → 1.1.2
  [dev/auth-service abcdef0] Bump v1.1.2

  $ git push origin dev/auth-service
  ...
  # → test-auth-service.yml fires; wait for green check.

  $ .github/scripts/package.sh
  Version : v1.1.2
  Workflow: package-auth-service.yml
  Ref     : dev/auth-service
  Triggered.

  # → package-auth-service.yml runs ~2-4 min and ends with a
  #   github-actions[bot] commit on dev/daemon:
  #
  #   Build: Update auth-service to v1.1.2

  # On dev/daemon: a pull surfaces the new auth-service under
  # services/auth-service/. The next phantom-daemon Docker build
  # picks it up automatically.


Rollback
--------

  Two paths:

  1. Bump again (patch) and re-package — fastest, leaves a clean
     forward-only history.

  2. Manually revert services/auth-service to a previous version on
     dev/daemon:

         git checkout dev/daemon
         git revert <hash-of-Build:-Update-auth-service-to-vX.Y.Z>
         git push

     The dev/auth-service branch is unaffected.


Notes
-----

  * services/auth-service/ on dev/daemon is owned by
    github-actions[bot]. Operators do not edit it directly. Source
    changes go to dev/auth-service, then ride through this pipeline.

  * The packager always builds from a clean dist/ (--clean flag).
    Stale files from a previous build cannot leak through.

  * The Sync step removes the target directory before copying, so
    files deleted from auth-service appear as deletions on dev/daemon
    too — there is no orphaned-file drift.

  * persist-credentials is intentionally true on the dev/daemon
    checkout (the workflow needs to push back) and false on the
    auth-service-src checkout (read-only here).

  * Consumers do not pull from this branch directly. The
    cross-branch commit pattern is what makes "where did this
    auth-service version come from?" trivially answerable on the
    daemon side: every change is a github-actions[bot] commit
    referencing the version.
